{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:27:49.749646+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 14cdb62b2e100f4ebf75f88cf5c58669437208e3)", "id": "lc_98240327-ebed-4c33-b9a5-8d3c1905005d"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# vue3-vite-starter-template\n\nA single page app [Vite](https://vitejs.dev) starter template, created to easily bootstrap Vue.js 3 apps.\n\n**Features**\n\n- Vitest for unit testing\n- Pinia for state management\n- Vue Router 4 for client-side routing\n- Bootstrap 5.3 for layout and styling\n- SCSS variables inside Vue components\n- Purgecss for eliminating unused CSS\n- Basic multiple layouts feature\n- ESLint config based on `eslint:recommended` with sensible defaults :relaxed:\n- [Prettier](https://prettier.io/) for code formatting\n- Automated release workflow with [semantic-release](https://github.com/semantic-release/semantic-release)\n\n## Project setup\n\n```\npnpm install\n```\n\n### Compiles and hot-reloads for development\n\n```\npnpm run dev\n```\n\n### Compiles and minifies for production\n\n```\npnpm run build\n```\n\n## Run your unit tests\n\n```\npnpm run test:unit\n```\n\n### Lints files\n\n```\npnpm run lint\n```\n\n### Lints and fixes files\n\n```\nnpm run lint-fix\n```\n\n### Customize configuration\n\nSee [Configuration Reference](https://vitejs.dev/guide/).\n", "id": "lc_a7fb59d4-0993-40dc-bb42-e05b02f3b7fc"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "91b6b713-6146-4ebd-a807-fb4d545bb72e", "tool_call_id": "call_6ab0a7f0623849bbb068115d", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:27:58.580996+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my analysis of the repository, **contributors are expected to use pnpm** and **npm is not acceptable**. Here's the evidence:\n\n## 1. **Package Manager Specification in `package.json`**\nThe `package.json` file contains:\n```json\n\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\"\n```\nThis explicitly declares that the project should use pnpm version 10.20.0.\n\n## 2. **Enforcement Mechanism**\nThe `package.json` includes a preinstall script that actively blocks npm:\n```json\n\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\"\n```\nThis script will run before any installation and will fail if you try to use `npm install`, `yarn`, or any other package manager. The `only-allow` package is specifically designed to enforce a single package manager.\n\n## 3. **Documentation in README.md**\nThe project setup instructions in `README.md` explicitly show:\n```\npnpm install\n```\nAll other commands are also documented with `pnpm`:\n- `pnpm run dev`\n- `pnpm run build`\n- `pnpm run test:unit`\n- `pnpm run lint`\n\n## 4. **Lock File**\nThe repository contains `pnpm-lock.yaml` (207KB), which is pnpm's lock file format, not `package-lock.json` (npm) or `yarn.lock` (yarn).\n\n## 5. **Node Version Specification**\nThere's also a `.nvmrc` file (which I can check if needed) that likely specifies a Node.js version, but this doesn't affect the package manager choice.\n\n## Conclusion\nThis repository is **strictly pnpm-only**. The combination of the `packageManager` field, the `preinstall` enforcement script, documentation showing pnpm commands, and the presence of `pnpm-lock.yaml` all confirm that npm is not acceptable. Contributors must use pnpm to contribute to this project.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 683, "prompt_tokens": 5080, "total_tokens": 5763, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 263, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4672, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0002614416, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 7.02016e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00019124}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871269-Ic7ZLw1Nkovy9K7MtBTJ", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea433-0d76-7650-a69f-bf13256cff37-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5080, "output_tokens": 683, "total_tokens": 5763, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 4672}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 263}}}}]}}}
